  The human karyotype | Back to Top

   There are 44 autosomes and 2 sex chromosomes in the human genome, for a total of 46. Karyotypes
   are pictures of homologous chromosomes lined up together during Metaphase I of meiosis. The
   chromosome micrographs are then arranged by size and pasted onto a sheet.

